column2:
First person: "Why did Don fly to Vancouver yesterday?"
Second person: “Did Carol discover that he’s Canadian?”
How certain is the second person that Don is Canadian?
column3:
First person: “Why did Bob refuse to pay Mary’s cab fare?"
Second person: “Did he realize that she’s wealthy?”
How certain is the second person that Mary is wealthy?
column4:
First person: “Why did Jessica walked away from Katia in the middle of their conversation?” 
Second person: “Did Jessica notice that Katia has bad breath?”
How certain is the second person that Katia has bad breath?
column5:
First person: "Why did you recommend this movie to me?"
Second person: "Do you know that the main actor is really famous?" 
How certain is the second person that the main actor from the movie is really famous?
column6:
First person: “Why did Rachel bring maple sirup to the party!” 
Second person: “Did she discover that the host is Canadian?”
How certain is the second person that the host is Canadian?
column7:
First person: “Why did Mary buy rounds of drinks at the bar last night?” 
Second person: “Did her boyfriend realize that she’s wealthy?”
How certain is the second person that Mary is wealthy?
column8:
First person: “Why did Dan bring a tooth brush to the party?” 
Second person: “Did Lily notice that Dan has bad breath?”
How certain is the second person that Dan has bad breath?
